items.summary: With U-Turn's timely demise Nancy and Conrad check the status on their debts and then they check in with each other. Someone is pregnant and they are keeping it. Doug continues to try to sabotage Celia and Celia continues to sabotage Nancy. Nancy celebrates something. Silas begins spending more time with Tara.
items.title: He Taught Me How to Drive By
items.titleSort: He Taught Me How to Drive By

items.summary: Celia and Sullivan step up their relationship. Andy gets more involved in a different business. Silas and Tara begin working together. Shane and Isabelle spend time together. Nancy meets Peter's other ex-wife, Valerie.
items.title: The Two Mrs. Scottsons

items.summary: Doug and Sullivan fight over a golf membership and Doug get some revenge. Nancy spends time with Valerie, who considers her an “insane stalker person”. Conrad and Silas spend time together. Dean is injured and hospitalized. Tara tries to get deeper into Nancy's business.
items.title: Release the Hounds

items.summary: Nancy's up and running again until someone betrays her and sends in the DEA. Celia spends more time with Dean. Doug has ethics decisions to make.
items.title: Roy Till Called

items.summary: Nancy discovers who betrayed her and  finds out she's being trailed. Some people lose their jobs. Silas discovers something about Tara. Shane installs a security system.
items.title: Cankles

items.summary: Andy and Dean play murderball. Nancy ponders a new venture while Heylia and Conrad must abandon theirs. Doug sinks to an all-time low.
items.title: The Dark Time

items.summary: Nancy tries out a new source but it doesn't go so well. Conrad and Nancy are having some good interplay. Heylia and Vaneeta like the new neighborhood. Celia is angry.
items.title: Risk

items.summary: Nancy has another full week of trouble to deal with and Doug isn't helping. Heylia teaches Celia.
items.title: Protection

items.summary: As the wildfire approaches, everyone must evacuate. Nancy tells her family to pack up, while Conrad and Heylia must say goodbye to the growhouse. The authorities question Sullivan and Celia, while Shane continues to ask Nancy about Pittsburgh. As Andy deals at the evacuation center, Silas realizes the truth about Tara.
items.title: Go

items.summary: Nancy has relocated to the border in search of a new life but she soon finds her past to be inescapable. Both problems and people follow her on her journey, but some have finally been left behind.
items.title: Mother Thinks the Birds Are After Her
items.titleSort: Mother Thinks the Birds Are After Her

items.summary: After settling her family in Ren Mar, Nancy turns her attention back to business. Later, Guillermo gives her a much-needed crash course in "running" across the border. Meanwhile, Celia gets further acquainted with life in prison. Lenny leaves Silas and Shane to care for Bubbie while he goes to the track. When Lenny returns, Andy confronts him about some family history.
items.title: Lady's a Charm

items.summary: Nancy makes her first successful smuggling run across the border with both drugs and human cargo. Meanwhile, Captain Till strikes a deal with Celia to get her out of jail. In return, she must gather evidence to incriminate Nancy and Guillermo. Back in Ren Mar, Andy tries to convince the family, including his father, to put Bubbie out of her misery.
items.title: The Whole Blah Damn Thing

items.summary: After Bubbie's death, the entire Botwin family sits shiva (the Jewish period of mourning) for seven days. After shiva, Nancy is sent on a mission and takes Andy along with her. Now that shiva is over and Bubbie is gone, Lenny decides to sell the house. Meanwhile, Celia continues her flirtation with Captain Till, and Doug finds refuge with the Botwins.
items.title: The Three Coolers

items.summary: Guillermo gives Nancy a new job and she soon finds working retail isn't as mundane as it appears on the surface. Celia's deal with Captain Till brings her dangerously close to the action. Meanwhile, having been left in the desert by Nancy, Andy finds himself with a pack of immigrants and a very unfriendly Coyote. Back at home, the boys battle an infestation of bees.
items.title: No Man is Pudding

items.summary: Nancy follows the tunnel in the back of the maternity shop and sees something she shouldn't at the other end. Dean takes a new job, leaving Isabelle to live with Celia. Meanwhile, Silas flirts with Lisa, and Doug falls in love with a vision of beauty who washes up on the beach.
items.title: Excellent Treasures

items.summary: When Nancy is denied a share of the incoming pot by Guillermo, she decides to go over his head to Esteban. Celia discovers the cheap medication at Mexican pharmacies. Silas and Lisa get intimate, while Shane discovers some shocking photos. Andy and Doug begin interviewing for their human smuggling operation.
items.title: Yes I Can

items.summary: A spontaneous date ends in near-violence for Nancy and Esteban; Silas reveals to Lisa that he grows pot, and she makes him a tempting offer; Andy and Doug smuggle their first customer across the border; Celia develops an addiction.
items.title: I Am the Table

items.summary: Despite their busy schedules, Nancy and Esteban try to find some time for each other. After finding out about Shane's fantasies and Silas's new and much older girlfriend, Nancy also has to talk to both of her sons. With their relationship going on, Lisa and Silas add some special offerings to her cheese shop.
items.title: Little Boats

items.summary: Nancy learns that the tunnel is being used for more than drugs. Esteban puts her fears to rest as well as her nagging headache with a strong remedy. Celia's family stages an intervention in order to force her into rehab. Andy finds Maria and takes her across the border to an awaiting Doug. Silas babysits while Shane explores new territory with his two girlfriends.
items.title: The Love Circle Overlap

items.summary: Nancy must deal with the aftermath of Shane's exploits, her Ayahuasca trip, and more confrontation with Guillermo. Celia's struggles with her rehab partner, Barry, force her to find a new rehab facility. Doug and Maria's relationship quickly goes south and they both turn to Andy for help. Meanwhile, Silas's "sandwich" business has grown too big, forcing him to turn to Nancy for help.
items.title: Head Cheese

items.summary: A fed up Nancy squeals to the DEA to bust the tunnel while she plays it cool with Esteban. Embracing rehab, Celia sets out to make amends with her family. Andy succumbs to Maria's advances, and later comes clean to Doug. Shane impresses his girlfriends with his drug scoring abilities.
items.title: Till We Meet Again

items.summary: The DEA brings Nancy in for questioning and then she must explain things to Esteban. Celia travels deep into Mexico to make amends with estranged daughter Quinn. Meanwhile, Silas meets Lisa's ex-husband and Doug finds a reason to live. Nancy makes a shocking revelation to Esteban.
items.title: If You Work For a Living, Then Why Do You Kill Yourself Working?
items.titleSort: If You Work For a Living, Then Why Do You Kill Yourself Working?

items.summary: After showing Esteban the proof of her baby, a sonogram picture. Nancy returns to Ren Mar to her family, but still unsure of her fate. Meanwhile, Celia is held hostage in Mexico by her estranged daughter Quinn who tries to ransom her off to all her friends, but they hilariously decline to deliver the cash for her release. Back in Ren Mar, Andy, Silas and Doug discuss plans to grow pot in a national forest.
items.title: Wonderful Wonderful

items.summary: Nancy pays a secret visit to Guillermo in prison; Celia puts her time in the rebel camp to good use by organizing their supplies; Shane decides to visit Nancy's estranged sister (Jennifer Jason Leigh); Silas and Doug second-guess their choice of a pot-growing plot.
items.title: Machetes Up Top

items.summary: Nancy gets a surprise visit from Jill; Nancy's bodyguard goes missing; Celia's micromanaging gets her sent back to the U.S.; Silas and Doug seek law enforcement approval.
items.title: Su-Su-Sucio

items.summary: Nancy is visited by DEA agent Roy Till who has gone rogue and homecomer Celia moves into Nancy's garage. Meanwhile, Andy tries to access his brother's old bank account.
items.title: Super Lucky Happy

items.summary: Nancy talks with her obstetrician about ending the pregnancy. After his teacher took his pot, Shane needs some help to get it back. Andy is still trying to get access to his late brother's bank account. Meanwhile, Silas and Doug need to see "The Wizard" to make their pot selling dreams come true.
items.title: Van Nuys

items.summary: It's six months since we last saw everyone and Nancy is in full bloom. Esteban proposes, and all seems right with the world until Nancy discovers there's another woman in Esteban's life. Andy, meanwhile, has gone on a spending spree and let himself go. Now he must come to terms with the new order of things. Celia, unhappy in her job at the mall, discovers an opportunity in the world of cosmetics. Shane spends an eye-opening day with Ignacio. Silas and Doug's medical marijuana dispensary is in full operation. But Deputy C.P. Jones continues his meddling ways.
items.title: A Modest Proposal

items.summary: Nancy learns the identity of the other woman in Esteban's life, as well as his plans for her childbirth delivery. With the help of Andy and Audra, Nancy takes matters into her own hands. Meanwhile, Celia discovers that getting rich quick isn't always so easy. Silas and Doug learn the hard way that Deputy C.P. Jones is more trouble than he's worth as the fate of their medical marijuana dispensary is jeopardized.
items.title: Where the Sidewalk Ends

items.summary: The tension between Nancy and Esteban mounts as Pilar adds to the conflict. Nancy looks to Andy for help, just as hes focused on his relationship with Audra. Dean offers to help Silas and Doug get their dispensary back on track, but Celia sees an opportunity and steps in.
items.title: A Distinctive Horn

items.summary: Nancy and Andy grow closer together while they try to be good parents. In the meantime, Celia and Dean work together to exploit their product surplus.
items.title: Suck 'n' Spit

items.summary: With the arrival of new enemies, Shane and Silas needs Nancy's protection. Meanwhile, Andy plans his future with Audra, while Doug and Dean make a plan to put an end to Celia's marijuana business.
items.title: Perro Insano

items.summary: A visit from Esteban's daughter comes with new problems for Nancy. In the meantime, Isabelle joins Doug and Dean's scheme of revenge against Celia.
items.title: Ducks and Tigers

items.summary: Nancy, Andy and Cesar team up to look for Esteban when he goes missing. In the meantime, Dean and Doug start their scheme of revenge against Celia, while Silas and Shane develop a need to protect their new stepsister.
items.title: Glue

items.summary: Nancy learns of Esteban's fate and takes action to preserve her own. Andy makes a big change in his life. Dean, Doug and Celia find common ground. Silas helps Adelita with a disturbing medical issue.
items.title: All About My Mom

items.summary: Faced with the aftermath of Shane having murdered Pilar, Nancy grabs Shane and Silas and they flee the scene. Andy is then met with the decision to split town with his family or stay and fight for Audra's affection.
items.title: Thwack

items.summary: After hours of aimless driving, Nancy, ignoring Shane's suggestion of hiding out in Pittsburgh, hatches a plan for the family to cross into Canada. Andy is tasked with acquiring fake IDs. Silas must decide if he's willing to live on the lam. Elsewhere, Esteban must answer to authorities regarding Pilar's murder and Nancy's whereabouts.
items.title: Felling and Swamping

items.summary: Nancy becomes a scab labor in a Seattle hotel while Shane looks after Stevie and Doug goes back to Ren Mar
items.title: A Yippity Sippity

items.summary: Nancy makes a deal with the concierge and Shane becomes part of a mommy group. Meanwhile, Doug is questioned by Cesar and Ignacio.
items.title: Bliss

items.summary: The Botwins' flight continues after a parking violation and Doug gets into a hostage situation.
items.title: Boomerang

items.summary: Nancy brings her son back while Andy and Silas wait in a diner.
items.title: A Shoe for a Shoe

items.summary: Nancy decides that her family has seen enough gunslinging for a lifetime, so to lighten things up she takes them to a Montana fair. Andy and Silas enter a butter-eating contest while Doug looks after the baby and makes friends with the carneys. Elsewhere, Nancy escorts Shane on a rollercoaster where they stir up some trouble in line.
items.title: Pinwheels and Whirligigs

items.summary: After acquiring an RV, Nancy lets Andy navigate the road and he leads them to Pioneer Town, a former western movie set now turned off-the-grid scab city. While Nancy attempts to get the lay of the land, she instructs the family to set up a mobile hash making shop inside the RV. Andy and Silas work on getting laundry machines while Doug and Shane try to obtain water.
items.title: Gentle Puppies

items.summary: Nancy is met with yet another roadblock when baby Stevie gets sick leaving her and Andy to scramble to find a pediatrician. Meanwhile, Silas, Shane and Doug are tasked with unloading some merchandise at a kiddie concert.
items.title: To Moscow, and Quickly

items.summary: Nancy, attempting to score some big cash, returns to her hometown where she takes up residence with Warren an old acquaintance. Andy and Doug try to secure information on where to locate fake passports. Meanwhile, Silas and Shane curiously dig into Nancy's past.
items.title: Dearborn-Again

items.summary: Nancy, trying to get she and her family out of the country, is continually faced with unexpected guests from her past. Andy has to get creative in order to secure passports while Doug must find his own means of obtaining one. Meanwhile, Silas deals with the possibility that Lars could be his father. Shane is left to deal with Warren who is becoming unhinged.
items.title: Viking Pride

items.summary: Nancy has a tense, one-on-one, sit-down interview with Vaughn. Andy, Shane and Warren to get more cash plus passports they'll need for the family to enter Europe. Silas continues to wrestle with the fact that Lars may be his father. Meanwhile, Doug returns to Agrestic to locate his passport.
items.title: Fran Tarkenton

items.summary: In the season 6 finale, Nancy must free herself from the grip of Esteban in order to escape the country along with her family. At the airport, Andy attempts to calm the nerves of Shane and Warren. Meanwhile, Silas must decide whether to stay with Lars or leave with the Botwins.
items.title: Theoretical Love Is Not Dead

items.summary: Three years after Nancy's selfless act to save her family, Andy, Silas, Shane and Doug live their new lives in Copenhagen. When Nancy is released early from prison and put on parole to a New York halfway house, she finds out that she doesn't need witness protection anymore.
items.title: Bags

items.summary: Nancy tries to get back on the right track after being released from prison, but faces a tough struggle living in New York City; Andy and Shane show up at Nancy's door, sending her for a loop and tempting her to go back to her old ways.
items.title: From Trauma Cometh Something

items.summary: Nancy struggles to fit into the ranks at the halfway house; Jill drops a bombshell; Andy and Shane find a place to live; Silas scores a modeling gig; Doug is offered his dream job.
items.title: Game-Played

items.summary: Nancy pursues a job at Doug's office; Andy may be in over his head; Shane tries to set up house; Silas attempts a partnership.
items.title: A Hole in Her Niqab

items.summary: Silas and Nancy's lawyer assist her in getting to California as her custody battle with Jill (Jennifer Jason Leigh) heats up. Meanwhile, Andy's relationship takes an intriguing turn; Shane decides to give it the old college try and enrolls in classes; and Doug is left to fend for himself at his job on Wall Street.
items.title: Fingers Only Meat Banquet

items.summary: Nancy confronts an old friend, leaving Silas caught in the crossfire; back at the loft, Andy comes up with a new business venture, and turns to Shane and Doug for help.
items.title: Object Impermanence

items.summary: While Doug plays softball with the company team, Nancy deals pot on the sidelines; Andy opens his bike shop while Silas sells pot out of the back room; and a police detective offers Shane an internship.
items.title: Vehement vs. Vigorous

items.summary: Nancy's former cellmate Zoya shows up and complicates things between Nancy and her supplier; Silas and Andy bang heads over how to best utilize the bike shop; and Shane's internship provides him with some surprising lessons.
items.title: Synthetics

items.summary: Nancy and Andy try to put the brakes on Zoya's attempt to take over the bike shop; Silas has an encounter with some local rival dealers; and Doug must do some business with the Securities and Exchange Commission.
items.title: Cats! Cats! Cats!

items.summary: Nancy, Andy and Silas strike back at Emma; Doug has to keep his hedge fund up and running; Shane ends up closer to the law.
items.title: System Overhead

items.summary: In an attempt to further expand her business, Nancy follows Doug and Andy to the Hamptons for the weekend; Silas tries to win Emma back after a falling out over business; Detective Ouellette brings Shane along on a drug bust.
items.title: Une Mère Que J'aimerais Baiser

items.summary: Nancy and Silas face off over who controls their drug business, while Andy tries to mediate; Shane goes to lengths to win back Detective Ouellette's trust, while Doug tries to keep the SEC distracted from his hedge fund's illegal activities.
items.title: Qualitative Spatial Reasoning

items.summary: In the Season 7 finale, Silas turns the tables on Nancy, as Shane makes one last attempt to keep her out of harm's way and the clutches of Detective Ouellette. Meanwhile, back on Wall Street, Doug schemes to keep his hedge-fund scam alive.
items.title: Do Her / Don't Do Her

items.summary: Nancy is rushed to the hospital after being shot as the family follows close behind. The family grapples with the tragedy and hypothesizes on the shooter's identity.
items.title: Messy

items.summary: Andy makes his intentions known to Jill. Doug is presented with an enticing investment opportunity. While Nancy recuperates, Silas helps her with a new business venture. Shane figures out who shot his mother.
items.title: A Beam of Sunshine

items.summary: Andy attempts to impress Jill by coaching the twin's roller-derby team; Doug ponders about his financial future after being forced to resign from the company; Nancy and Silas race to thwart Shane's actions, who is closing in on Tim.
items.title: See Blue and Smell Cheese and Die
items.titleSort: See Blue and Smell Cheese and Die

items.summary: Despite the demands of her marijuana business, Nancy decides to throw a family dinner, to which Shane invites his classmate Angela. In other pot news, Silas befriends a local grower. Meanwhile, Jill and Andy agree to watch Stevie during the day.
items.title: Only Judy Can Judge

items.summary: Nancy is tempted to go back to her old pot-dealing ways to raise cash for Stevie's soccer expenses; Jill gets revenge on Andy through Doug; Shane and Angela double-date with Ouellette and his wife; Silas and R.J.'s friendship takes an unusual turn.
items.title: Red in Tooth and Claw

items.summary: Nancy undertakes a job search; Jill has big news for Andy and Doug; and Silas tries to track down his stolen plants. Meanwhile, Shane fabricates an ingenious plan to score some extra spending money at the police academy.
items.title: Allosaurus Crush Castle

items.summary: Andy visits a local synagogue to look for work while Nancy gets a quite competitive new job and Shane is ready to graduate from the police academy.
items.title: Unfreeze

items.summary: After receiving an interesting proposal from an unexpected source, Nancy struggles with a decision involving a questionable business.
items.title: Five Miles From Yetzer Hara

items.summary: A "cowboy capitalist" moseys into town with a tasty offer for Silas; and rumors spread about Rabbi Dave having an amorous encounter with a nonmember of the synagogue.
items.title: Saplings

items.summary: Silas contemplates a big professional move; Nancy has a dinner date with Rabbi Dave and some of his friends; and Andy experiences a slight hitch in his relationship status.
items.title: Threshold

items.summary: Nancy, Andy and Silas take a trip. Shane is busted for stealing property off the impound lot. Meanwhile, Doug gives up on his charity and decides to pursue a bigger, more lucrative scheme.
items.title: God Willing and the Creek Don't Rise
items.titleSort: God Willing and the Creek Don't Rise

items.summary: The Botwins (& Doug) are at a crossroads, romance-wise and professionally.
items.title: It's Time (1)

items.summary: The Boreal forest of Northern Canada is a vast tract of wilderness stretching from the Atlantic Ocean to the Pacific. It is home to moose and beaver, crisscrossed by rivers and lakes and frost-free for only about three months of the year. Les intentionally tips his canoe in mid-stream and crawls from the icy waters onto shore where he does a quick inventory of his supplies. A handful of cashews and beef jerky, a solitary match, a multi-tool and 50 lbs of camera equipment to document the next seven days in the bush.
items.title: Canadian Boreal Forest

items.summary: The Sonora Desert in the South-Western United States covers an area of approximately 120,000 square miles. It is an arid, seemingly barren environment with scorching daytime highs and freezing overnight lows. Riding a dirt bike out into the official middle of nowhere, Les simulates a break-down scenario. He empties out the contents of his pack - half a gallon of water, a snack bar and his multi-tool-7 more days!
items.title: Arizona Desert

items.summary: A Costa Rican getaway - as far removed from everyday living as you can imagine: lush rainforests and deserted tropical beaches. Marooned on Costa Rica's Osa Peninsula, Les "Survivorman" Stroud has only a few items to aid him for the next 7 days: swimming goggles, 3 ballpoint pens, a multi-tool and the clothing on his back. On top of the keeping hydrated in the intense humidity and relentless heat, Les must cope with deadly snakes, enormous spiders, land-crabs and scorpions.
items.title: Costa Rica

items.summary: The swamplands of Georgia's Altamaha River Basin are all that one would expect of a Primordial bog: dank, menacing, swimming with slithering creepy-crawlies and, of course, alligator-infested. This is the welcoming environment Les Stroud will be immersed in for seven sweaty days and bone-chilling nights.
items.title: Georgian Swamp

items.summary: Pond Inlet, on the Northern reaches of Baffin Island, provides one of the most challenging landscapes our planet has to offer. Over 700km north of the Arctic Circle, it sits amidst grinding, ever-shifting flows of sea-ice where polar-bears roam in search of meat. In this severe climate, Les has been equipped with a bare minimum of raw materials to aid him for the next 7 days - a hunk of uncooked seal-liver, some oil-rich blubber for heat, a seal-hook, three matches, and a knife.
items.title: Canadian Arctic

items.summary: Les is airdropped onto a snow-covered peak in the Canadian Rockies courtesy of the Canadian Mountain Air Rescue Service. They'll come looking for him in seven days. Until then Les is entirely on his own, save for the grizzlies, cougars and wolves that also call this place home. To emulate a real-life survival scenario - in this case a heli-hiking expedition come to grief - Les has been provided with a few readily salvageable items, among them a broken camcorder and tripod. One man's trash is another man's treasure!
items.title: Canadian Rockies

items.summary: The spectacular red landscapes of Utah's canyonlands are as beautiful as they are inhospitable. Like outlaws of old who were known to eat their own horses out of desperation in this forlorn place, Stroud will cannibalize the mountain-bike he has ridden into the middle of nowhere. As well as these scavenged bike parts to aid him, he also has a multi-tool, a magnesium flint-stick and an old energy-bar - that he has a use for other than eating.
items.title: Utah Canyonlands

items.summary: In the remote winter-bound forests of Northern Ontario, a crashed plane lies in the snow beside a frozen lake. There is no one alive on board. But this plane didn't crash here - the decrepit old wreck has been airdropped from a helicopter to provide a temporary home for Survivorman. For a week Les will have to survive in this harsh snowy wilderness with only an axe, a multi-tool and a single blanket to aid him.
items.title: Plane Crash

items.summary: Living "off the land" takes on a new meaning as Les Stroud casts off for a week at sea. With no food and only a bare minimum of equipment, Stroud will be set adrift in an inflatable life raft off the coast of Belize. Battling hunger, thirst and the Caribbean heat, he must also keep his cameras dry to film the ordeal. To top it off - the life raft has a few bad leaks and needs constant bailing. It also leaks air and requires frequent re-inflation with a hand pump - Survivorman is in for a busy few days!
items.title: Lost at Sea

items.summary: Just when you think it can’t get any hotter, Les Stroud finds out it can. In this episode, Les dips his toes in the scorching red sands of the Kalahari Desert — one of the most extreme climates on Earth.
items.title: Kalahari Desert

items.summary: The phrase “It’s a jungle out there” takes on a whole new meaning when Les Stroud pays a visit to one of the densest, deepest parts of the Amazon jungle. For seven days, Les “Survivorman” Stroud will test his mettle, his will and his ingenuity — everything he’s got — to survive in one of the most dangerous places on Earth.
items.title: Ecuador

items.summary: For this episode, Les Stroud goes to the dogs — literally. Our intrepid Survivorman relies on seven Inuit sled dogs (Labrador huskies) to pull his dog sled into the wilds of Labrador. He embarks on this dangerous journey at the tail end of winter, when the weather is the most unpredictable.
items.title: Labrador

items.summary: The plains of South Africa conjure up images of beauty — and danger. In this episode, Les Stroud lands here for an arid adventure that would make even the most seasoned safari traveler sweat. And not just because of the heat.
items.title: African Plains

items.summary: This time Survivorman decides to demonstrate survival by sea kayak in an ocean bay called Taroka Arm (literally "black bear") for good reason. At this time of year, the salmon are active and are one of the black bear's favorite foods. Black bear and grizzlies that live in this area are among the largest in the world and gorge themselves on the silver salmon during this period.
items.title: Alaska

items.summary: Les demonstrates survival in the Cook Islands using SCUBA gear, a ship wreck and found articles.
items.title: South Pacific

items.summary: Les explains his preparation for each locale in this behind the scenes look at the episodes of season 2.
items.title: Behind the Scenes

items.summary: Les tries to survive in the Sierra Nevada Mountains in California. This time he has more than just his trusty harmonica and his multi tool, He also has some basic backpacking gear as well like a tent, a sleeping bag, and a flashlight. When he doesn’t show up at camp his team is forced to organise a Search and Rescue team to find him. Will they find him in time?
items.title: Sierra Nevada

items.summary: "Survivorman" Les Stroud takes two horses into the Colorado Rockies and discovers the challenges of surviving for three.
items.title: Colorado Rockies

items.summary: Stranded on northern Baffin Island, "Survivorman" Les Stroud learns harsh lessons in solo arctic survival in 24hour daylight.
items.title: Arctic Tundra

items.summary: Survivorman Les Stroud finds himself scrounging to feed two people after a hunting trip goes wrong.
items.title: Temagami Hunting - Deep Woods

items.summary: Les Stroud is stranded in the outback when his ultralight airplane runs out of fuel.
items.title: Australian Outback

items.summary: Les Stroud must survive in the jungles of Papua New Guinea.
items.title: Papua New Guinea

items.summary: Les Stroud strands himself in the Norwegian mountains to survive for ten days taking little food, no water or gear, and no safety or camera crew.
items.title: Norway Mountain - Part 1

items.summary: Les Stroud is stranded in the Norwegian mountains. Surviving for ten days, Les has no food supplies and little water. Alone and exhausted, Les tests the will to live like never before.
items.title: Norway Mountain - Part 2

items.summary: Les Stroud is shipwrecked on the desert island of Tiburon. With limited food supplies and no fresh water, Les scavenges to survive on the desert shore.
items.title: Tiburón Island Coast – Part 1

items.summary: Les Stroud is shipwrecked on the desert island of Tiburon. Avoiding packs of wild coyotes, scorpions and rattlesnakes, he treks in-land in search of food, water and shelter.
items.title: Tiburón Island Coast – Part 2

items.summary: With all the ground Les has covered, it's little wonder there's a dark side. Hope you weren't one of the people on that canoe trip; and it's hard to imagine what he'd do if he happened on a litterbug.
items.title: Survivorman's Top Ten

items.summary: Les must survive for 5 days in the jungle on the island of Grenada
items.title: Grenada Jungle

items.summary: Les must survive for 5 days on Frigate Island in the Grenadines
items.title: Frigate Island

items.summary: Les Stroud travels to the Mitre Peninsula, a remote peninsula located on the easternmost tip of Isla Grande in the province of Tierra del Fuego, Argentina.
items.title: Tierra del Fuego

items.summary: Les Stroud travels into the forests of Ontario's Temagami, and the oldest mountains in North America to survive for 5 days, with no food, no water, no shelter, and no crew.
items.title: Temagami Forest

items.summary: Les teaches winner of a fan submission contest, amateur filmmaker Joseph McConnell, about wilderness survival in the remote Ontario wilderness.[8][9][10]
items.title: Fan Challenge

items.summary: Les Stroud disappears into the thickly forested Transylvanian Alps to test the skills of Romania's top search and rescue team, and himself.
items.title: Transylvania - Part 1

items.summary: Les simulates a broken leg so that a Romanian search and rescue team will locate him in the Transylvania mountains.
items.title: Transylvania - Part 2

items.summary: The story of a family that was lost in the forests of Oregon for six days.
items.title: Oregon

items.summary: Les travels to Northern India in the foothills of the Himalayans to survive in an area with the world's reported densest tiger population.
items.title: India: The Himalayan Foothills

items.summary: Les and his friend Bob Wilson are stranded on a deserted island in the archipelago of Tonga.
items.title: Tonga

items.summary: Les retraces the last steps of experienced Argentine hiker Laureano Emanuel Santos on the circuit track of Torres del Paine National Park in Chilean Patagonia to investigate how tragedies can occur even on well-traveled wilderness trails.[11]
items.title: Patagonia

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 01 - Pilot.avi
items.summary: After suffering a series of mysterious anxiety attacks, New Jersey mob boss Tony Soprano agrees to see a psychiatrist, Dr. Jennifer Melfi. As he opens up to the doctor, Tony reveals details about his problems at home and at work that involve his wife Carmela, his kids Meadow and Anthony Jr., his Uncle Junior and his domineering mother Livia.
items.title: The Sopranos

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 02 - 46 Long.avi
items.summary: With acting boss Jackie Aprile dying of cancer, Tony prepares for a power struggle with Uncle Junior. Christopher and his associate Brendan make trouble for themselves when they jack a truck full of DVD players. Tony's mother Livia finally agrees to live in a retirement community. Big Pussy and Paulie Walnuts are sent to find a stolen car.
items.title: 46 Long

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 03 - Denial, Anger, Acceptance.avi
items.summary: Uncle Junior's associate Mikey Palmice stirs things up by making Junior think Tony wants to be next in line for boss. Meanwhile, Tony, Paulie and Silvio deal with Hasidic family problems.
items.title: Denial, Anger, Acceptance

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 04 - Meadowlands.avi
items.summary: Jackie Aprile's health worsens, forcing Tony to make a tough decision. Meanwhile, Anthony Jr. learns the true nature of his father's job in 'waste management.' Also, Tony hires sleazy police lieutenant Vin Makazian to investigate Dr. Melfi's background.
items.title: Meadowlands

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 05 - College.avi
items.summary: During a trip to Maine for Meadow's college interviews, Tony sees a man he believes is a relocated mob snitch. Back at home, Carmela receives comfort from Father Phil.
items.title: College

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 06 - Pax Soprana.avi
items.summary: At Tony's suggestion, Junior is made acting boss after Jackie dies. In therapy, Tony surprises Dr. Melfi with an admission. Carmela and Irina (Tony's mistress) both suffer as Tony's libido takes a nosedive.
items.title: Pax Soprana

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 07 - Down Neck.avi
items.summary: After stealing the 'sacramental wine' from the school chapel, Anthony Jr. is suspended. Tony is concerned that his bad influence is responsible for his son's behavior, and has a series of disturbing flashbacks in which he remembers learning that his own father was in the mob.
items.title: Down Neck

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 08 - The Legend of Tennessee Moltisanti.avi
items.summary: At the wedding of Larry Boy's daughter, the 'boys' find out they're going to be indicted, and make a premature exit to get rid of incriminating evidence at home. Upset that he isn't getting the notoriety of other family members, an agitated Christopher has an ugly encounter with a bakery clerk.
items.title: The Legend of Tennessee Moltisanti

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 09 - Boca.avi
items.summary: Uncle Junior enjoys a romantic tryst in Boca with his girlfriend Bobbi, not realizing that she's been gabbing to her beauty-parlor friends about his oral talents. Meanwhile, controversy arises when Meadow's soccer coach announces he's leaving the school.
items.title: Boca

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 10 - A Hit Is a Hit.avi
items.summary: Christopher and Adrianna cut a deal with a famous gangsta rapper who claims that Hesh pocketed royalties belonging to a cousin who recorded several hit songs decades ago. Meanwhile, Tony plays golf with Cusamano and his white-bread friends.
items.title: A Hit Is a Hit

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 11 - Nobody Knows Anything.avi
items.summary: After Jimmy and Pussy are arrested in an FBI raid, Makazian tells a stunned Tony that Pussy may be wired for the Feds. Tony sends Paulie to find out for sure. Later, Tony learns that Makazian might be trying to frame Pussy to get out of his gambling debts.
items.title: Nobody Knows Anything

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 12 - Isabella.avi
items.summary: Hit men are sent out to whack Tony, who comes out of his depression when he meets Isabella, an Italian exchange student staying next door.
items.title: Isabella

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 1/The Sopranos Season 1 Episode 13 - I Dream of Jeannie Cusamano.avi
items.summary: In the Season One finale, Tony is stunned to discover that the attempt on his life may have been ordered by someone very close to him. Later, he must deal with the fact that everyone knows he is seeing a shrink. Christopher is sent to take care of Jimmy Altieri.
items.title: I Dream of Jeannie Cusamano

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 01 - Guy Walks into a Psychiatrist's Office.avi
items.summary: Season Two opens with the aftermath of the federal crackdown: Junior's in jail, Melfi refuses to see Tony, Christopher's expanding into new business ventures, Pussy is still missing...and Tony's adjusting to life as the new boss. To complicate matters even more, Tony's free-spirited sister Janice arrives to take care of Livia.
items.title: Guy Walks into a Psychiatrist's Office
items.titleSort: Guy Walks into a Psychiatrist's Office

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 02 - Do Not Resuscitate.avi
items.summary: When black protesters start picketing a construction company that used to be under Uncle Junior's control, Tony meets with the owner--as well as the leader of the protestors--to 'fix' the problem. Meanwhile, Janice gets sucked into Livia's web.
items.title: Do Not Resuscitate

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 03 - Toodle-fucking-oo.avi
items.summary: Tony busts Meadow for partying at his mother's old house. Meanwhile, Ritchie Aprile is out of the can after ten years and looking for action--much to the chagrin of a local pizza-shop owner.
items.title: Toodle-Fucking-Oo

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 04 - Commendatori.avi
items.summary: Tony travels to Italy with Paulie and Christopher to jump-start a car-importing 'business.' While Paulie and Christopher sample some of the Old Country's choicest wares, Tony haggles with the head of a powerful Naples family and recruits a valuable new lieutenant named Furio.
items.title: Commendatori

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 05 - Big Girls Don't Cry.avi
items.summary: Back in Jersey, Furio soon lives up to his name by unleashing his fury on the delinquent proprietor of a local 'tanning salon.' Dr. Melfi shares her guilt over dumping Tony as a client during a session with her own therapist. Meanwhile, Tony learns from Hesh that his father had emotional secrets of his own.
items.title: Big Girls Don't Cry

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 06 - The Happy Wanderer.avi
items.summary: David Scatino, the father of Meadow's friend Eric and the owner of a local sports store, gets on the bad sides of both Richie and Tony when he loses big in two poker games. Paying his respects at a funeral, Tony is forced to deal with the presence of Livia.
items.title: The Happy Wanderer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 07 - D-Girl.avi
items.summary: With Anthony Jr.'s confirmation approaching, Tony and Carmela find their son's growing apathy a cause for concern. Meanwhile, Christopher's interest in show biz is reignited when he meets a well-known filmmaker through his cousin's girlfriend.
items.title: D-Girl

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 08 - Full Leather Jacket.avi
items.summary: Although Richie is miffed at Tony for forcing him to build a ramp for the pizza-parlor owner he paralyzed, he decides to make a peace offering. Unhappy with their lowly status as Christopher's lackeys, Sean and Matt decide to pledge their allegiance to Richie--through a violent, unexpected act.
items.title: Full Leather Jacket

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 09 - From Where to Eternity.avi
items.summary: Christopher has an out-of-body experience that spooks Paulie to no end. Carmela urges Tony to have a vasectomy. Visiting her own psychiatrist, Melfi reveals the 'unholy alliance' she's made with Tony...as well as her growing dependence on pills and alcohol.
items.title: From Where to Eternity

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 10 - Bust-Out.avi
items.summary: Richie meets with Tony to complain about his end of the garbage business, then meets with Junior to complain about Tony. Later, Tony orchestrates the 'planned bankruptcy' of David Scatino's sporting-goods store while Scatino's wife introduces Carmela to her handsome widowed brother.
items.title: Bust Out

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 11 - House Arrest.avi
items.summary: Having dodged a legal bullet, Tony is advised by his lawyer to spend more time at his businesses. Junior looks for diversions to relieve the tedium of house arrest, and eventually finds one in the company of a police widow. Meanwhile, Melfi's problems boil over while eating dinner with her son.
items.title: House Arrest

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 12 - The Knight in White Satin Armor.avi
items.summary: Engaged lovebirds Richie and Janice have an explosive first quarrel. Meanwhile, Irina takes drastic measures to try to convince Tony to continue their affair.
items.title: The Knight in White Satin Armor

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 2/The Sopranos Season 2 Episode 13 - Funhouse.avi
items.summary: In the Season Two finale, Tony has a series of 'fever dreams' that help to shed light on some of his problems--particularly his troubles over Big Pussy.
items.title: Funhouse

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 01 - Mr. Ruggerio's Neighborhood.avi
items.summary: While the Soprano family goes about their day-to-day activities, the FBI begins an elaborate operation to bug their home. Tony ponders his options when Patsy starts asking too many questions about his brother's death.
items.title: Mr. Ruggerio's Neighborhood

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 02 - Proshai, Livushka.avi
items.summary: Tony's concerns that his mother will rat him out to the feds expire when she, literally, does. Later, Janice arrives to arrange the funeral, which takes a bizarre turn.
items.title: Proshai, Livushka

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 03 - Fortunate Son.avi
items.summary: Christopher finds that being a 'made' man isn't all it's cracked up to be. Meanwhile, Janice moves into her mother's house, where she soon gets a leg up on Livia's former housekeeper.
items.title: Fortunate Son

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 04 - Employee of the Month.avi
items.summary: Dr. Melfi's attempts to steer Tony into behavior-modification therapy take a detour when a personal crisis gets in the way. Meanwhile, Ralph Cifaretto finds a way to endear himself to Jackie Jr.--but not to Tony.
items.title: Employee of the Month

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 05 - Another Toothpick.avi
items.summary: Bobby 'Bacala' Baccilieri Sr. comes out of retirement to deal with a young hothead named Mustang Sally--much to the chagrin of his son and Uncle Junior.
items.title: Another Toothpick

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 06 - University.avi
items.summary: Ralph's volatile relationship with a Bada Bing stripper and his obsession with the movie 'Gladiator' combine to put a damper on several boys'-nights-out sessions at the club. Meanwhile, at Columbia, Meadow's relationship with Noah is put to the test by her needy roommate Caitlin.
items.title: University

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 07 - Second Opinion.avi
items.summary: Tony convinces Uncle Junior to seek a second opinion for his cancer treatment. Meanwhile, Carmela debates whether or not to take Dr. Melfi's advice and see a shrink, Big Pussy's wife Angie regrets asking Carmela for some money to help her sick dog, and Christopher continues to endure a humiliating probation period at the hands of kinky Paulie.
items.title: Second Opinion

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 08 - He Is Risen.avi
items.summary: As Thanksgiving approaches, Tony's feud with Ralph escalates, despite the intervention of Johnny Sack. At a frat-house mixer, Meadow and Jackie Jr. find they have more in common than mob-boss dads.
items.title: He Is Risen

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 09 - The Telltale Moozadell.avi
items.summary: Tony gives Carmela a sapphire ring for her birthday...and Christopher gives Adriana her very own music club. Anthony Jr. gets busted for vandalizing the school swimming pool, but finds the punishment doesn't fit the crime. Tony test-drives a new Mercedes--and the Mercedes saleswoman, Gloria.
items.title: The Telltale Moozadell

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 10 - To Save Us All from Satan's Power.avi
items.summary: A somnolent visit with the ghosts of Christmas past lands Tony back on Melfi's couch. With the annual pork-store holiday party approaching, Bacala reluctantly agrees to don the Santa suit that Pussy used to wear. Tony and Furio have a holiday surprise in store for the Russian who roughed up Janice.
items.title: To Save Us All from Satan's Power
items.titleSort: To Save Us All from Satan's Power

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 11 - Pine Barrens.avi
items.summary: Paulie and Christopher are engulfed in a nightmarish journey into the South Jersey woods while trying to collect a debt from a Russian mobster. Meanwhile, Meadow is suspicious that Jackie Jr. is two-timing her, and Tony finds that family demands are jeopardizing his romance with Gloria.
items.title: Pine Barrens

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 12 - Amour Fou.avi
items.summary: Inspired by a tale from Ralph about how his father got 'made,' Jackie Jr. decides to 'make his move' in organized crime by instigating a robbery caper at a local card game. Reminded by Melfi of the psychological parallels between his relationships with Gloria and with his mother, Tony finds it harder and harder to spend time with his 'crazy love.'
items.title: Amour Fou

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 3/The Sopranos Season 3 Episode 13 - Army of One.avi
items.summary: Yet another academic misstep by A.J. forces his parents to contemplate military school. Tony orders Ralph to deal personally with the Jackie Jr. situation, and later seems to take Ralph's side in a money dispute with Paulie. Once again, the family gathers in Artie Bucco's restaurant, where Meadow reflects on being a Soprano.
items.title: Army of One

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 01 - For All Debts Public and Private.avi
items.summary: Tony invests in a land deal despite Carmela's concerns about money. Junior faces his own financial woes as his trial approaches. Adriana brings her new friend to the Soprano Sunday dinner, but Adriana has no idea who Danielle is working for. Tony bonds with Christopher by giving him the opportunity to avenge the murder of his father.
items.title: For All Debts Public and Private
items.titleSort: For All Debts Public and Private

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 02 - No Show.avi
items.summary: With Paulie in jail, Christopher becomes acting capo, but he gets off to a bad start with Patsy. Still troubled by Jackie Jr.'s death, Meadow contemplates taking a year off from college to travel. Meanwhile, Adriana is in a bind after ending her friendship with Daniele, and Silvio discusses a misunderstanding at a Newark riverfront construction site.
items.title: No-Show

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 03 - Christopher.avi
items.summary: Silvio and Ralph must take care of a planned protest of the Columbus Day parade by a Native American group. At an Italian pride ladies' lunch, Carmela is embarrassed by anti-Mafia remarks. Meanwhile, Ralph deals with new relationship troubles, and Bobby receives some tough news.
items.title: Christopher

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 04 - The Weight.avi
items.summary: A disparaging remark about his wife sets Johnny Sack off on a vendetta. Meadow decides to do volunteer work at the South Bronx Law Center; Furio hosts a housewarming party for the gang; Silvio and Chris make an offer to an old-time hit man named Lou DiMaggio; and Tony and Carmela find themselves at odds over the family's bill-consolidation strategy.
items.title: The Weight

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 05 - Pie-o-My.avi
items.summary: Checking out Ralph's promising new filly at the track, Tony displays a flair for horse-racing strategy--and discovers an unexpected affinity for the stable life. Adriana finds her rock club being used as a place of business for Chris and his pals. Meanwhile, a court artist incurs the wrath of Uncle Junior, and Janice feeds Bobby in his hour of need.
items.title: Pie-O-My

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 06 - Everybody Hurts.avi
items.summary: After hiring an attractive French hostess, Elodi, Artie agrees to loan her brother some money, with interest. Meanwhile, Christopher gets some new responsibilities; Carmela fixes Furio up with an oral hygienist; Anthony Jr. becomes the 'dough boy' of a new rich girlfriend; and Tony receives some unsettling news about an old acquaintance.
items.title: Everybody Hurts

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 07 - Watching Too Much Television.avi
items.summary: Tony and the gang throw Paulie a Bada Bing bash after his release from jail, but it doesn't take long for old tensions to resurface. Carmela's cousin Brian throws out a hypothetical investment scenario that Tony and Ralph attempt to turn into reality with the help of Assemblyman Zellman and a black community leader.
items.title: Watching Too Much Television

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 08 - Mergers and Acquisitions.avi
items.summary: Paulie takes pains to integrate his mother Nucci into the social world at Green Grove. Meanwhile, Furio faces up to his inner feelings during a trip to Italy to see his ailing father; Ralph introduces Tony to his new 'goomar,' Valentina; and Carmela finds a new source of investment income.
items.title: Mergers and Acquisitions

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 09 - Whoever Did This.avi
items.summary: After an aggressive team of reporters lowers the boom on Uncle Junior, his lawyers try a new strategy. Ralph has some fun at the expense of Paulie and his mother, but soon winds up with his own family problems. Meanwhile, Tony again finds refuge at the stables.
items.title: Whoever Did This

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 10 - The Strong, Silent Type.avi
items.summary: At therapy, Tony likens himself to the 'sad clown,' but Melfi doesn't buy into his melancholy portrait. Meanwhile, Carmela drags A.J. with her to Furio's house to offer decorating tips and companionship; Paulie puts the finishing touches on some free artwork; and Christopher finds himself at a crossroads.
items.title: The Strong, Silent Type

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 11 - Calling All Cars.avi
items.summary: After a sitdown with Carmine and Johnny Sack, Tony contemplates the future of the HUD partnership. Meanwhile, Paulie blows off steam with an old pal; Janice starts losing patience with the obsessive Bobby; and Melfi ponders the Freudian undercurrents of Tony's latest dreams.
items.title: Calling All Cars

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 12 - Eloise.avi
items.summary: Tony continues to haggle with Johnny Sack and the two Carmines over the Esplanade profits. Carmela makes a decorating date she can't keep; Furio proves a reluctant companion to Tony on a casino junket; Paulie plays an impatient chaperone to some ladies from the nursing home; and Meadow debates the true meaning of a literary classic with her mom.
items.title: Eloise

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 4/The Sopranos Season 4 Episode 13 - Whitecaps.avi
items.summary: In the Season Four finale, Tony and Carmela contemplate purchasing a shore house, but a voice from the past threatens the deal. While Uncle Junior breaks out the Hearty Burgundy, Little Paulie and Benny break in a new sound system on the Stugots. With Carmine apparently intent on putting the past behind him, Tony and Johnny Sack weigh their options, carefully.
items.title: Whitecaps

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 5/The Sopranos Season 5 Episode 01 - Two Tonys.avi
items.summary: A flood of organized crime parolees changes the landscape of the Soprano/Lupertazzi alliance. Janice carries on the family's Sunday dinner tradition. Carmela and A.J. commune with local wildlife. Christopher balks at footing the bill on 'goomar night.' Tony tries to introduce Dr. Melfi to his 'other' self.
items.title: Two Tonys

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 5/The Sopranos Season 5 Episode 02 - Rat Pack.avi
items.summary: Tony sizes up a contractor's gift, then reunites with his paroled cousin, Tony Blundetto. Paulie and Christopher relive some not-so-special memories. Carmela launches a film club. Adriana grapples with her guilt. A familiar figure 'crosses over.'
items.title: Rat Pack

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 5/The Sopranos Season 5 Episode 03 - Where's Johnny.avi
items.summary: Tony's power-sharing plan doesn't fly with Johnny Sack, who makes his point through a bookie named Lorraine Calluzzo. Out on parole, Feech La Manna crosses Paulie in his attempt to break into the landscaping business. Tony gets a roommate. Junior looks into the past while testing the patience of those closest to him.
items.title: Where's Johnny?

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 5/The Sopranos Season 5 Episode 04 - All Happy Families.avi
items.summary: Carmela and Tony reunite, if only to discuss Anthony Jr.'s dwindling college prospects. Feech takes Tony's crew on a trip down memory lane. Lorraine's allegiances get her into hot water. A.J. has a night to remember in the Big Apple.
items.title: All Happy Families

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 5/The Sopranos Season 5 Episode 05 - Irregular Around the Margins.avi
items.summary: While Christopher is away, Tony gives Adriana a ride home that proves disastrous. Meanwhile, the Soprano crew plays a game of 'telephone' with the story that turns it into something far more sinister when an enraged Christopher gets wind of it.
items.title: Irregular Around the Margins

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 5/The Sopranos Season 5 Episode 06 - Sentimental Education.avi
items.summary: With her son's future at stake, Carmela puts in some extra time with his college advisor, Robert Wegler. Meanwhile, Tony Blundetto realizes it's hard doing business with strangers, and A.J. concludes there's no place like home.
items.title: Sentimental Education

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 5/The Sopranos Season 5 Episode 07 - In Camelot.avi
items.summary: His father's longtime goomar sheds light on some of Tony's lingering emotional and financial mysteries. Meanwhile, Junior sees the upside of attending the funerals of fringe relations, while Christopher sees the downside of enabling an A.A. friend's new addiction.
items.title: In Camelot

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 5/The Sopranos Season 5 Episode 08 - Marco Polo.avi
items.summary: Friends and family gather at the Sopranos' for a not-so-surprise 75th birthday party for Carmela's father, Hugh. Meanwhile, Johnny Sack shows off his new wheels, Phil Leotardo pulls into Pussy's old place for some auto repairs, and Tony B. considers accepting a familiar job on the side.
items.title: Marco Polo

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 5/The Sopranos Season 5 Episode 09 - Unidentified Black Males.avi
items.summary: A rumor involving his cousin puts Tony's relationship with Johnny Sack back on thin ice. Meadow helps get her boyfriend Finn a job. A.J. ponders a 'maximum-security summer' at Casa Carmela. Melfi links Tony's current guilt to a past job. Carmela learns that good legal help is hard to find.
items.title: Unidentified Black Males

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 5/The Sopranos Season 5 Episode 10 - Cold Cuts.avi
items.summary: Tony B. and Christopher unearth some old memories during an otherwise idyllic trip to the country. Tony and Carmela plan another party. Janice lands in anger-management therapy after a sports-rage incident. Benny and Terry solve a missing-Vespa mystery. Tony puts his sister's newfound serenity to the test.
items.title: Cold Cuts

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 5/The Sopranos Season 5 Episode 11 - The Test Dream.avi
items.summary: Tony escapes to the Plaza Hotel for a night of rest and relaxation, but his dreams are haunted by past faces. Another casualty falls in the war between Johnny Sack and Little Carmine, and Tony B. heads to New York for revenge.
items.title: The Test Dream

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 5/The Sopranos Season 5 Episode 12 - Long Term Parking.avi
items.summary: With the feds pulling a new trump card, Adriana ponders her options. Tony B. unloads some heavy baggage on Tony, and vice-versa. Johnny Sack makes Tony an offer he can refuse, and Tony offers Carmela a deal to make her real-estate dreams come true.
items.title: Long Term Parking

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 5/The Sopranos Season 5 Episode 13 - All Due Respect.avi
items.summary: In the Season Five finale, Tony's crew circles the wagons as Johnny Sack turns up the heat. Carmela counts her blessings. Christopher is freaked out by an unexpected visitor. Benny's connection to the plumber's union comes in handy. A.J. demonstrates his business acumen. Tony ponders whether to execute a 'sacrifice bunt.'
items.title: All Due Respect

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 01 - Members Only.avi
items.summary: Gene Pontecorvo makes a final break from the mob life, while Junior's paranoid delusions could be the end of Tony.
items.title: Members Only

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 02 - Join The Club.avi
items.summary: The family tries to cope with Tony's hospitalization and possibly impending death, while Tony begins to hallucinate a new life parallel to his own.
items.title: Join the Club

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 03 - Mayham.avi
items.summary: While the gang begins to turn on itself, Tony finds himself at the threshold.
items.title: Mayham

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 04 - The Fleshy Part of the Thigh.avi
items.summary: Tony goes home and returns to business, perhaps with a new frame of mind. Paulie receives a shock about his mother.
items.title: The Fleshy Part of the Thigh

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 05 - Mr. & Mrs. John Sacrimoni Request....avi
items.summary: Johnny Sack asks for permission to get out of jail for his daughters wedding; Tony's on the look out for personal protection.
items.title: Mr. and Mrs. Sacramoni Request

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 06 - Live Free or Die.avi
items.summary: Tony seeks guidance from overseas to solve a local problem; and decides whether a top earner deserves another chance.
items.title: Live Free or Die

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 07 - Luxury Lounge.avi
items.summary: Chris meets and beats the stars, while Artie turns violent after having his hospitality abused.
items.title: Luxury Lounge

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 08 - Johnny Cakes.avi
items.summary: Vito considers starting a new life in New Hampshire, while Anthony continues his pursuit of revenge against Junior.
items.title: Johnny Cakes

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 09 - The Ride.avi
items.summary: Paulie finds public opinion turned against him after an amusement ride accident, while Chris tries to start a new life as a husband and father.
items.title: The Ride

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 10 - Moe 'n' Joe.avi
items.summary: Tony reflects on how growing up with Janice colors his attitudes now, while Vito tries to make a new life for himself in New Hampshire.
items.title: Moe n' Joe

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 11 - Cold Stones.avi
items.summary: Phil takes out his revenge on Vito, while Tony grows frustrated with Anthony's lack of ambition or work ethic.
items.title: Cold Stones

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 12 - Kaisha.avi
items.summary: Phil Leotardo seeks to continue a cycle of retaliation between the New York and Jersey families. Christopher wrestles with his addictions. Tony decides keeping Carmela occupied with the spec house is for the best. A.J. gets a new girlfriend.
items.title: Kaisha

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 13 - Sopranos Home Movie.avi
items.summary: Bobby and Janice host a wild 47th birthday bash for Tony at their Adirondacks vacation home. Tony's actions following Johnny Sack's arrest come back to haunt him.
items.title: Soprano Home Movies

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 14 - Stage 5.avi
items.summary: Christopher's Cleaver premieres, showing Tony how he feels about him. Johnny Sack faces a health crisis. Phil Leotardo resents his family, and himself, for being weak and downtrodden. Silvio gets caught up in New York's power vacuum.
items.title: Stage 5

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 15 - Remember When.avi
items.summary: When Tony's first hit is about to be unearthed, he and Paulie flee to Florida, where Tony contemplates their friendship. Junior organizes a poker game at the institution. The New York power struggle continues.
items.title: Remember When

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 16 - Chasing It.avi
items.summary: Maria Spatafore requests help from Tony for Vito, Jr. Tony's bad luck puts a rift between he and Hesh. A.J. makes a major choice regarding his future.
items.title: Chasing It

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 17 - Walk Like a Man.avi
items.summary: The relationship between Christopher and Paulie's falters, while A.J. grows depressed over his break-up with Blanca.
items.title: Walk Like a Man

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 18 - Kennedy and Heidi.avi
items.summary: The Soprano and Lupertazzi crime families quarrel over asbestos removal. Tony deals with a problematic associate. Paulie suffers a devastating personal loss. A.J. questions his friendship with Jasons Parisi and Gervasi.
items.title: Kennedy and Heidi

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 19 - The Second Coming.avi
items.summary: Tony attempts to repair the rift between New Jersey and New York. A.J.'s depression struggle continues. A New York associate crosses the line with Meadow.
items.title: The Second Coming

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 20 - The Blue Planet.avi
items.summary: The spectre of disloyalty among the crew hangs over Tony as Phil Leotardo decides how to handle recent issues with the Soprano crime family. A hit gone wrong comes at a huge cost. A.J.'s conquering of his depression is challenged.
items.title: The Blue Comet

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Sopranos/Season 6/The Sopranos Season 6 Episode 21 - Made in America.avi
items.summary: Tony seeks to find a peace with the Leotardo crew while dealing with rumors a member of his own crew may have flipped. A.J. makes a decision regarding his future and Junior's slide into dementia continues.
items.title: Made in America

items.summary: After his business partner cheats a dangerous client, financial adviser Marty must devise a radical plan to save the lives of himself and his family.
items.title: Sugarwood

items.summary: In the Ozarks, Marty struggles to find a local business he can use for money laundering, while his kids make new friends but neglect a crucial duty.
items.title: Blue Cat

items.summary: Marty finds a way to control Ruth. Wendy worms her way into a job. Looking for another business to invest in, Marty digs for info on the strip bar.
items.title: My Dripping Sleep

items.summary: Marty hires Ruth to pull off a heist. Agent Petty forges a relationship with a member of the Langmore family. Jonah exhibits disturbing behavior.
items.title: Tonight We Improvise

items.summary: Marty decides to invest in the religious sector, unaware he will disrupt a discreet business operation. A surprise visitor shows up at the Byrde home.
items.title: Ruling Days

items.summary: Jacob educates Marty on his business. Ruth devises and sets in motion a deadly plan. Rachel learns Marty is cooking the books at the Blue Cat Lodge.
items.title: Book of Ruth

items.summary: To stop Jacob from carrying out his threat, Marty makes an offer. Agent Petty gets what he needs to turn Russ. Charlotte grows desperate to escape.
items.title: Nest Box

items.summary: In a flashback to 10 years prior, Wendy struggles with depression, Del asks Marty to be his financial adviser, and Agent Petty faces a family crisis.
items.title: Kaleidoscope

items.summary: Russ learns Agent Petty's true identity and makes plans to murder, steal and flee. Wendy stumbles on an ideal business to add to the Byrde portfolio.
items.title: Coffee, Black

items.summary: During his next sermon, Mason falters. Wendy and the kids are caught trying to flee their home. Marty brokers a deal between Jacob and Del.
items.title: The Toll

items.summary: Ruth's dad gets out of jail. Approval for a riverboat casino calls for Wendy's political skills. The Mexican cartel demands reparations from the Snells.
items.title: Reparations

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Ozark/S02/Ozark S02E02 The Precious Blood of Jesus.mkv
items.summary: When a mobster jeopardizes the casino bill, Marty enlists Buddy's help. Wendy resorts to dirty tactics to get votes. Cade reminds Ruth of her roots.
items.title: The Precious Blood of Jesus

items.summary: Wendy does damage control when Wilkes's pressure on Sen. Blake backfires. Rachel is sent on a mission. Ruth resists accepting her Langmore destiny.
items.title: Once a Langmore...

items.summary: The FBI sends out a second lure. Charlotte slips up while chatting with Wyatt. The Byrdes grow wary of Rachel, who deflects suspicion onto someone else.
items.title: Stag

items.summary: Agent Petty's revelation tests the loyalties of Marty, Ruth and the cartel. Despite the FBI closing in, the Snells refuse to destroy their poppies.
items.title: Game Day

items.summary: An FBI search of the Snells' field yields a surprise. Playing hardball, Agent Petty questions Wilkes. The Byrdes mourn a loss.
items.title: Outer Darkness

items.summary: Mason goes off the deep end and focuses his rage on the Byrdes. Ruth tries to make her dad proud during a boat-part heist.
items.title: One Way Out

items.summary: Darlene makes one too many rash moves. Marty tries to free Rachel from Agent Petty's grasp. Jonah helps his mom force Wilkes to continue his support.
items.title: The Big Sleep

items.summary: Marty finds a way around the Snells. Charlotte hires a lawyer. The Byrdes get a meeting with the gaming commission, whose approval comes with a big ask.
items.title: The Badger

items.summary: Marty makes plans without telling Wendy. Darlene sends a message via Jonah. Wyatt learns the truth about his dad. Ruth realizes Cade must be stopped.
items.title: The Gold Coast

items.summary: Marty and Wendy wrestle with a problematic offer. Ruth goes out on her own, Jonah rebels, and Omar's nephew makes his presence known.
items.title: The Beginning of the End

items.summary: Maya pushes back on Marty's plan for Omar. Ruth pursues the hipster heroin market. Wendy tries to raise $150 million. The new sheriff causes problems.
items.title: Let the Great World Spin

items.summary: Maya and Omar meet face-to-face. Wendy has a contentious business meeting. Ruth goes behind Darlene's back. Jonah finds a new place to set up shop.
items.title: City on the Make

items.summary: Wendy's claims about Ben anger Ruth. Mel the P.I. tracks down Wendy's father. Ruth's trip to the Missouri Belle with Kerry doesn't go as planned.
items.title: Ace Deuce

items.summary: The Senator extends an olive branch — with a twist. Ruth and Marty scramble to rebuy the drugs Darlene sold. Charlotte ponders life after high school.
items.title: Ellie

items.summary: Marty is tasked with proving Omar wasn't involved with a bombing. Wendy pays a visit to the Lazy-O Motel. Ruth and Wyatt make a plan.
items.title: Sangre Sobre Todo

items.summary: The FBI's long-awaited meeting with Omar takes place. Wyatt shares some news with Ruth. Feeling betrayed, Javi gets aggressive.
items.title: Sanctified

items.summary: Devastated by a tremendous loss, Ruth heads to Chicago to enact revenge as Marty tries to talk her out of doing something she may regret.
items.title: The Cousin of Death

items.summary: Their deal with the FBI now dead, the Byrdes desperately search for more solutions to their growing problems. Wendy’s father comes to town.
items.title: Pick a God and Pray

Later, Mare bumps heads with locals and airs concerns about her grandson Drew in light of her late son’s mental health struggles.

items.summary: House is faced with a problem he may not be able to solve and Stacy returns.
items.title: Honeymoon

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 01 - Acceptance.avi
items.summary: When a Death Row inmate mysteriously and  suddenly collapses after hallucinating, House jumps at the chance to  take the case for its difficulty and because it's "cool."
items.title: Acceptance

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 02 - Autopsy.avi
items.summary: A girl's unimaginable bravery toward her terminal illness makes House suspicious as he puts a life-or-death decision about her case in her young hands.
items.title: Autopsy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 03 - Humpty Dumpty.avi
items.summary: Cuddy struggles with a case of guilt when her handyman is injured while at her place, and House and his team have to work fast to save the young man's pursuit of the American Dream.
items.title: Humpty Dumpty

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 04 - TB Or Not TB.avi
items.summary: House's patient is willing to die in order to further his social cause.
items.title: TB or Not TB

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 05 - Daddy's Boy.avi
items.summary: Lies between a father and son may prevent House and his team from saving their patient.
items.title: Daddy's Boy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 06 - Spin.avi
items.summary: House's wheels start turning when a pro-cyclist admits to taking performance-enhancing drugs.
items.title: Spin

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 07 - Hunting.avi
items.summary: A patient with AIDS stalks House to get him to take his case; House and Stacy stalk a mouse in her attic; and Cameron faces a health scare of her own.
items.title: Hunting

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 08 - The Mistake.avi
items.summary: A patient's death prompts an investigation into whether Chase or House may have been responsible for her death.
items.title: The Mistake

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 09 - Deception.avi
items.summary: With Foreman as House's supervisor, the team must figure out if a woman who cried wolf  too many times is really ill.
items.title: Deception

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 10 - Failure to Communicate.avi
items.summary: A journalist's head injury results in unintelligible speech, leaving House and his team at a loss; and the heat is turned up between House and Stacy when they're out of town.
items.title: Failure to Communicate

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 11 - Need To Know.avi
items.summary: While House's staff tries to diagnose a woman whose uncontrollable muscle flailing caused her to crash her car, House and Stacy try to resolve their relationship issues once and for all. Cameron refuses to take her HIV test, wary of the results.
items.title: Need to Know

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 12 - Distractions.avi
items.summary: While a severely burned teenager is admitted and his blood tests come back with strange results, House makes himself the guinea pig in his own unofficial tests of a new drug designed to treat migraines to prove a former medical school colleague is wrong about the drug.
items.title: Distractions

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 13 - Skin Deep.avi
items.summary: House uncovers a startling secret when he treats a teenage supermodel for heroin addiction. Meanwhile, Wilson hopes the increased leg pain in House's leg is an indication his leg nerves are regenerating.
items.title: Skin Deep

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 14 - Sex Kills.avi
items.summary: House takes the case of a man who experienced a seizure but wasn't aware it happened. When the man suffers a heart attack and needs a heart transplant, the team races to diagnose a dead woman's illness so they can harvest her heart to save their living patient.
items.title: Sex Kills

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 15 - Clueless.avi
items.summary: House believes a woman is trying to kill her husband and tries to find the proof to confirm his suspicions. When Wilson moves in with House after separating from his wife, he learns Wilson is a great cook.
items.title: Clueless

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 16 - Safe.avi
items.summary: A teenage heart transplant patient is rushed to the hospital when she has an allergic reaction while living in a "clean" room, and House and Wilson work out the kinks of their new living arrangement.
items.title: Safe

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 17 - All In.avi
items.summary: When a six-year-old boy is brought in with the same symptoms as another patient who died years ago under House's care, House believes the cases are identical and he can predict the course of the boy's illness. Meanwhile, the clinic hosts a poker night to benefit the oncology department.
items.title: All In

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 18 - Sleeping Dogs Lie.avi
items.summary: House has to work fast when a woman comes in with a life-threatening case of insomnia. Meanwhile Cameron is angry at Foreman for stealing an article she worked on.
items.title: Sleeping Dogs Lie

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 19 - House Vs God.avi
items.summary: House treats a 15 year old faith healer, while Wilson feels left out when he finds out House has a weekly poker game.
items.title: House vs. God

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 20 - Euphoria (Part 1).avi
items.summary: When a police officer with a gunshot wound to the head and uncontrollable laughter is admitted, House and the team are baffled. When Foreman begins showing the same symptoms, they race to determine the cause of the illness before Foreman's condition takes the same path.
items.title: Euphoria (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/House MD/Season 2/House MD Season 2 Episode 21 - Euphoria (Part 2).avi
items.summary: Foreman continues to experience the same progression of symptoms as the police officer. When he realizes he may be facing imminent death, he calls his father who comes to his son's side.
